                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 MacVeagh, Lincoln/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 11, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. The Greek Minister has informed the Department that shortly after King George
                    returns to Athens he will invite the Chiefs of Mission to meet him in audience.
                    The Minister has expressed the hope that you will be authorized to join with
                    your colleagues in this ceremony although there will not have been time to
                    provide you with new letters of credence or for new letters of credence to have
                    been presented by him.</p>
                <p>It is the Department’s desire that you attend this ceremony unless the
                    representatives of the guaranteeing powers do not propose to be present, in
                    which case you should communicate with the Department for further
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
